<body>
  <h2>Day 1: Introduction to Digital Marketing</h2>

  <h3>Multiple Choice Questions</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>What is digital marketing?</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>A type of traditional marketing</li>
        <li>Marketing products or services using digital technologies</li>
        <li>A new form of advertising</li>
        <li>A strategy to increase website traffic</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Which of the following is NOT a digital marketing channel?</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Social media marketing</li>
        <li>Email marketing</li>
        <li>Print advertising</li>
        <li>Search engine marketing</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>What is the primary goal of digital marketing?</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>To increase brand awareness</li>
        <li>To generate leads and sales</li>
        <li>To improve customer engagement</li>
        <li>All of the above</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>What is SEO?</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Search Engine Optimization</li>
        <li>Social Engine Optimization</li>
        <li>Site Engine Optimization</li>
        <li>Search Engine Organization</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>What is PPC?</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Pay Per Click</li>
        <li>Pay Per Conversion</li>
        <li>Pay Per Click-Through</li>
        <li>Pay Per Commission</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h3>True/False Questions</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Digital marketing is only for large businesses.</li>
    <li>Social media marketing is a free marketing channel.</li>
    <li>Email marketing is a great way to build customer relationships.</li>
    <li>SEO is a one-time effort.</li>
    <li>PPC advertising can be a very effective way to generate leads.</li>
  </ol>
</body>
